    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "That's a good summary of the safety concerns. On the other hand, I've also been reading a lot about the \"accelerationist\" view—the idea that heavy regulation might actually do more harm than good by slowing down innovation or letting less ethical actors take the lead. How do you weigh the necessity of these existential risk regulations against the argument that they might stifle progress or be counterproductive?",
